        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el06",
          "type"         :"callout",
          "subtype"      :"misunderstanding",
          "format"       :"HTML",
          "eyebrow"      :"Common Misunderstanding",
          "term"         :"Addiction",
          "question"     :"<ul><li>What do you picture when you hear this word?</li><li>Does it include you – or does it feel like a word for other people?</li><li>Think of your own answer first, then look at ours.</li></ul>",
          "answer"       :"<p>Most people picture addiction as something extreme and visible – alcohol dependency, hard drugs, a life in obvious crisis. This makes it easy to conclude: <em>that's not me.</em></p><p>But the Bible's account of the problem doesn't divide people into addicts and non-addicts. It describes a heart that reaches for the wrong things to meet real needs – and that keeps reaching even when the cost is clear. By that account, the dynamic is far more universal than the stereotype suggests.</p><p>This series uses the word broadly and deliberately. You don't need to identify with the clinical definition to find yourself in these chapters.</p>",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
        },

        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el07",
          "type"         :"text",
          "subtype"      :"bridge",
          "format"       :"plainText",
          "text"         :"When the Bible talks about the heart, it does not simply mean our emotions. In biblical terms, the heart is the whole of the inner person – the place where we think, feel, desire, decide, and worship. It is the essential self.",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
        },

        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el08",
          "type"         :"biblePassage",
          "format"       :"HTML",
          "bibleRef"     :"Proverbs 4:23",
          "translation"  :"NET",
          "passageText"  :"<sup>23</sup>Guard your heart with all vigilance, for from it are the sources of life.",
          "passageUrl"   :"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Proverbs+4&version=NET",
          "bottomPadding":"none"
        },

        {
          "elementId"        :"ch01-el09",
          "type"             :"question",
          "format"           :"plainText",
          "question"         :"What is the heart's relationship to our behaviour?",
          "linkedPassage"    :"Proverbs 4:23",
          "answerType"       :"freeText",
          "required"         :false,
          "answerPlaceholder":"Your thoughts...",
          "bottomPadding"    :"normal"
