        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el10",
          "type"         :"text",
          "subtype"      :"bridge",
          "format"       :"plainText",
          "text"         :"If the heart is the fountain from which all behaviour flows, then our addictive behaviour is an expression of what the heart wants. External solutions – better habits, stricter accountability, environmental controls – can reduce opportunity and manage behaviour. They cannot change what we love. Only God can do that.",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
        },

