          "format"       :"plainText",
          "text"         :"Where the Respect dynamic drives people toward performance and achievement, the Rescue dynamic is experienced by those who have, in some sense, given up on the project of proving themselves. The self-loathing is too deep, the sense of failure too pervasive. What they are looking for is not admiration – it is simply acceptance. Not a verdict of 'excellent,' but a verdict of 'OK.'\n\nAnd the addiction offers exactly that. It does not judge. It is always available, always welcoming. For the person drowning in shame, it feels, in the moment, like grace. What it is, of course, is a counterfeit grace. And like all counterfeits, it is recognisable by what it fails to do: it offers the feeling of acceptance without any of its substance. It receives us as we are and leaves us exactly as we are.",
