          "text"         :"If the longing for relationship is God-given and good, why does it so often drive us toward things that harm us? Part of the answer is that genuine intimacy is costly. To be truly known requires vulnerability – and vulnerability means risk. The risk of exposure, of judgment, of rejection. The risk that if someone saw the full truth of us, they might not stay.\n\nOne of the things that addictive behaviour offers – across a wide range of different behaviours – is a simulation of intimacy without the risk. The warmth of alcohol in a social setting lowers inhibition and creates a feeling of connection without requiring the hard work of genuine relationship. Pornography offers the feeling of being desired and welcomed, at zero relational risk.",
