          "text"         :"There is a person who has sat through the previous seven sessions of this series. They have recognised themselves – perhaps painfully, perhaps with relief – in one or more of the dynamics we have explored. They have understood the framework. They have agreed, at least intellectually, that God offers more than the thing they keep reaching for. They have prayed, with complete sincerity, that this time will be different.\n\nAnd then they went home and did the thing anyway.\n\nThis chapter is for that person. It is also, in one way or another, for everyone in the room – because the gap between understanding the Gospel and being changed by it is one of the most common and most distressing experiences in the Christian life. If you have sat through seven sessions and still feel stuck, you have not misunderstood something. You have discovered something true: that information, on its own, is not enough.",
