          "question"     :"<ul><li>What do you think of when you hear this word?</li><li>What do you think it really means?</li><li>Think of your own answer first, then look at ours.</li></ul>",
          "answer"       :"<p>The word 'sanctification' rarely appears in conversation, but the idea is straightforward: becoming more holy over time. The misunderstanding is treating it as a self-improvement project – trying harder, behaving better, managing sin more effectively.</p><p>But sanctification is more like a plant growing than a machine being upgraded. The life is already there. The task is staying connected to the source – not generating growth through willpower, but remaining in the One from whom growth comes.</p><p>This chapter is the destination the series has been building toward: not just freedom from addiction, but conformity to the image of Christ. That is a larger and more beautiful goal – and it is entirely God's work, done in us as we cooperate with the means he has provided.</p>",
