          "type"         :"text",
          "subtype"      :"bridge",
          "format"       :"plainText",
          "text"         :"The reordering of our desires – the slow shift from finding our deepest satisfaction in counterfeits to finding it in God – is not something we can manufacture through effort. It is the work of the Holy Spirit, given to every believer. The Spirit does not simply help us to obey. He progressively reshapes what we want – slowly conforming our desires to God's own desires. This is sanctification. We cooperate with it, but we do not perform it. The pressure is off. The work is his.",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
        },

